data.enText: the piece of string in the centre of a candle which you light so that the candle burns
the piece of material in an oil lamp which absorbs the oil and which you light so that the lamp burns

tr: a loosely woven cord (in a candle or oil lamp) that draws fuel by capillary action up into the flame
any piece of cord that conveys liquid by capillary action
example: the physician put a wick in the wound to drain it

value.def: The wick of a candle is the piece of string in it which burns when it is lit.
The wick of a paraffin lamp or cigarette lighter is the part which supplies the fuel to the flame when it is lit.
value.tran: （煤油灯的）灯芯;（打火机的）棉芯

value.def: If you say that someone or something gets on your wick, you mean that they annoy and irritate you.

example.ex: The Professor was beginning to get on Molly's wick.
example.tran: 教授快要把莫莉惹毛了。
